Defendant Andrew Michael Hansen in court with attorney Douglas J. Rebholz.  Defendant Andrew Michael Hansen in custody.  
Katrina Voge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.
Competency hearing held. Sworn for the State: Dr. Jenna Goebel. Testimony closed. Statements by parties.  Court finds that the defendant is incompetent to proceed at this time, but if provided with appropriate treatment, is likely to become competent within the statutory time frame.  Court orders proceedings suspended.   Court ordered defendant committed to the Department of Health and Family Services for Institutional Care in order to restore competency.  Court recommended the defendant be evaluated for out of custody restoration to competency treatment.  Case is adjourned to Br. 1.  Return on Doctor's Report scheduled on 11/01/22 at 8:30.

Andrew Michael Hansen appeared by video means with Attorney.  Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.
